A quick way to
access normal mode command
from insert mode

Why?
- efficient
- control undo point
- control ctrl-u behaviour

How?
- alt or meta key + normal mode command
- ctrl-o

It's showtime!

The weird alt-a

Suggestion
" Ref: https://vi.stackexchange.com/a/2363/34851
if !has('nvim') | execute "set <M-a>=\ea" | endif
inoremap <M-a> <C-o>a

Weirdo alt-~

Suggestion
if !has('nvim') | execute "set <M-~>=\e~" | endif
inoremap <M-~> <C-o>~<C-[>

End
